WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Every developer knows this feeling.

00:03.000 --> 00:09.000
You ship a feature, users love it, and then the support ticket start.

00:09.000 --> 00:12.000
How do I use this? Where's the documentation?

00:12.000 --> 00:15.000
You look at your help docs. They're six months out of date.

00:15.000 --> 00:20.000
Here's the thing. We all know documentation matters, but nobody wants to write it,

00:20.000 --> 00:24.000
so we don't, and our users suffer.

00:24.000 --> 00:28.000
What if your documentation wrote itself?

00:28.000 --> 00:33.000
This is supportpages.io. You connect your GitHub repo just like that,

00:33.000 --> 00:39.000
and our AI reads your entire code base. It understands your product, your features, your users.

00:39.000 --> 00:42.000
Now watch what happens. You merge a pull request.

00:42.000 --> 00:49.000
Instantly, supportpages analyzes the change, not what code changed, what changed for your users,

00:49.000 --> 00:56.000
and it writes a help article, a real one, with steps, with screenshots, ready to publish.

00:56.000 --> 01:01.000
You review it. One click to approve, one click to publish, done.

01:01.000 --> 01:07.000
Your documentation is now always up to date. Every feature, every update, automatically.

01:07.000 --> 01:15.000
And your users, they get a beautiful help center, with search, with AI chat that actually answers their questions.

01:15.000 --> 01:19.000
No more writing docs at midnight. No more. We'll update that later.

01:19.000 --> 01:24.000
No more frustrated users. You ship code. We ship the docs.

01:24.000 --> 01:28.000
That supportpages.io.

